President Obama issued a statement on the occasion of Ramadan, sending warm greetings to Muslims observing the holy month of fasting. He acknowledged that Ramadan is a time for families and communities to come together for iftars and prayers, showcasing the rich traditions of Muslim societies. He also emphasized the spiritual aspect of Ramadan, highlighting the importance of reflection, renewal, and gratitude towards God. The President recognized the acts of charity and compassion that take place during Ramadan, both globally and within the United States. He expressed his appreciation for American Muslims who serve their communities and engage in inter-faith activities. President Obama concluded by expressing his anticipation of the annual White House iftar dinner, where American Muslims are welcomed to celebrate Ramadan and recognize their contributions to the country. The statement ends with the phrase "Ramadan Kareem," which is a traditional greeting for the holy month.